Package weloveclouds.server.client.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICommand
    Represents an object (command) that can be executed.
    IValidatable
    Interface for objects which can be validated.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractServerCommand
    Represents a command that is received from the CLI and is executed by the ServerCLIHandler.
    CacheSize
    A cacheSize command which sets the size of the cache (KVCache).
    ClientPort
    The port on which the server is going to listen to KVClients.
    DefaultCommand
    An unrecognized command.
    EcsPort
    The port on which the server is going to listen to ECS.
    Help
    Prints the help message of the server-side CLI.
    LogLevel
    LogLevel command which means setting the log level to the respective value.
    Quit
    Quit command which terminates the application.
    ServerCommandFactory
    CommandFactory design pattern, which gives a common handling mechanism of different commands.
    ServerPort
    The port on which the server is going to listen to other KVServers.
    Start
    StartNode command which starts the Server} based on the configuration in Start.context.
    Start.Builder
    Builder pattern for creating a Start instance.
    StoragePath
    The path for the KVPersistentStorage} where it can persist the records.
    Strategy
    The displacements strategy to be used in the KVCache}.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ServerCommand
    Different commands which are handled by weloveclouds.server.models.commands.ServerCommandFactory.
